[SN]TITLE[SN]
Paris St-Germain 2-0 Montpellier

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Paris St-Germain went top of Ligue 1 with victory over Montpellier, although they have now played two games more than title rivals Monaco.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Monaco, who face Juventus in the Champions League semi-finals, will return to the top on goal difference if they win at Lyon on Sunday (20:15 BST).
Edinson Cavani opened the scoring for the champions with his 31st league goal of the season from close range.
And he provided a backheel to set up Angel di Maria's brilliant 25-yard strike for the second.
PSG are aiming for their fifth French league title in a row.
